OOEOTOMA. Octotoma, Suffrian, Wiegm. Archiv, 1866, i. p. 2343 Horn, Trans. Am. Ent. Soc. x. p. 299.

The species of this peculiar genus may be at once known from any other American form by the strongly raised anastomosing ridges which extend irregularly over the whole disc of the elytra. The different species are very closely allied, and it will require long careful study‚ and the examination of a long series of each specific form, to define accurately their proper limits. The genus ranges from the United States of North

America to Brazil.
